'==================================================================
' OSINT AUTOMATION TOOL v2.5.2
'
' Changelog v2.5.0 -> v2.5.2:
'
'   v2.5.1 (flag cleanup)
'   - Stripped "--disable-features=...,VizDisplayCompositor,..."
'     from the headless cmdline - it was forcing the slow legacy
'     rasterizer and was the main perf regression vs v2.4.5.
'   - Also dropped --disable-breakpad, --disable-translate,
'     --disable-ipc-flooding-protection, --disable-hang-monitor
'     (marginal or net-negative in our tests).
'
'   v2.5.2 (architecture + retry)
'   - Cross-entity batching: customer + all CP tasks are added to
'     ONE flat queue and dispatched through a single 3-worker pool.
'     Old code drained the pool between entities (tail-idle); new
'     code keeps all 3 workers saturated end-to-end.
'   - CAPTCHA retry: after the initial pass, any task whose PDF is
'     > MIN_PDF_SIZE_BYTES but < CAPTCHA_SIZE_HINT (150 KB) is
'     retried once after a 15 s cooldown. Final success count is
'     re-computed from actual on-disk sizes.
'   - TIMING_PROFILE default switched to FAST (0.7x internal
'     waits). Switch back to NORMAL if VDI shows instability.
'
' Changelog from v2.4.5 -> v2.5.0:
'
'  Bucket 1 - Correctness
'  ----------------------
'   - Fixed audit-log "Total Searches" bug (accumulator was wiped
'     and rebuilt via OneDrive file enumeration, which silently
'     returned 0 while sync was pending).
'   - Added global ErrorHandler: unexpected errors now log to the
'     Audit_Log sheet and show a user dialog instead of silently
'     exiting via GoTo CleanExit.
'   - SharePoint-sync failures are now surfaced in the success
'     dialog instead of silently skipped.
'   - baseFileName trailing underscore stripped (happened when
'     alertID was blank -> produced filenames like
'     "ECM123__Customer_1...").
'   - Double-space in customer/CP names no longer triggers a false
'     "middle name detected" prompt.
'
'  Bucket 2 - Safe speed wins
'  --------------------------
'   - DNS/TLS warmup moved to BEFORE user prompts and made
'     asynchronous (fire-and-forget), so the handshake completes
'     while the analyst is filling in prompts.
'   - WshShell is created once in the main sub and reused by every
'     headless Edge launch (was re-created per search).
'   - Headless window size reduced from 1920x1080 -> 1280x900.
'   - Added hardening flags: --disable-breakpad, --mute-audio,
'     --hide-scrollbars, --password-store=basic,
'     --use-mock-keychain, --metrics-recording-only,
'     --disable-hang-monitor, --disable-default-apps,
'     --disable-component-update, --no-pings,
'     --disable-ipc-flooding-protection, --disable-translate.
'   - Added --virtual-time-budget=8000 so headless treats 8s of JS
'     timers as having elapsed immediately.
'   - SharePoint push moved to AFTER the folder open, so the
'     analyst sees the ECM folder without waiting for WebDAV.
'   - URLEncode hex now zero-padded (%0A instead of %A).
'
'  Bucket 3 - Architectural speed win
'  ----------------------------------
'   - Parallel 3-worker headless dispatch, scoped per-entity.
'   - Each worker uses its own --user-data-dir
'     (OSINT_EdgeWorker_0 / _1 / _2) so profile locks don't
'     collide between concurrent msedge.exe instances.
'   - Non-blocking wsh.Run launches + file-poll completion
'     detection (file exists AND size > MIN_PDF_SIZE_BYTES).
'   - 0.4 s launch stagger to stay under Google rate limits.
'   - 60 s per-task timeout. Orphans are left to self-exit.
'
' Expected runtime: ~3x faster than v2.4.5 on V2 Cloud
' (2 vCPU / 16 GB). A typical 50-search run drops from
' ~4:30 to ~1:30.
'
' To run: Assign "SearchAndSavePDF_Direct" to your macro button.
'==================================================================

Option Explicit

